Call.documentation: Transfers control to a Sub procedure or Function procedure

Option Explicit.documentation: Used at script level to force explicit declaration of all variables in that script.

On Error Resume Next.documentation: Specifies that when a run-time error occurs, control goes to the statement immediately following the statement where the error occurred and execution continues

On Error Goto 0.documentation: Disables any enabled error handler in the current procedure.

Property Get.documentation: Property procedure, which gets the value of a property.

Property Let.documentation: Property procedure, which assigns a value to a property.

Property Set.documentation: Property procedure, which sets a reference to an object.

ReDim.documentation: Used at the procedure level to reallocate storage space for dynamic array variables.

Step.documentation: Amount counter is changed each time through the loop. If not specified, step defaults to one.
